race.comment: Some key scratchings has left the door wide open for SHISUTA BO (5). She's on the quick back-up having run well at this track and distance last Saturday. As is custom, she will roll forward and take some catching, especially with the 3kg claim. THERMODYNAMIC (6) has been knocking on the door for a while now, rattling home last start over this track and trip to be 0.2L from the winner. On the quick turnaround today and he drops slightly in weight for this being a slightly tougher assignment. Big chance if he can run up to his latest figures. VAN ROY (7) bounced back last start at Warrnambool with a 0.8L defeat when leading over the 1700m journey. He drops back in trip now, but looks well placed on the back of that performance and he can be in this for a long way. SAN LUCIDO (10) has to be included after a strong performance on the main track here a fortnight ago.
